[4] Honduras
Date: Tue 2 Oct 2007
Source: Prensa Latina [edited]
<http://www.plenglish.com/Article.asp?ID=%7BAE152665-B759-4D57-A61F-17F00EA67702%7D&language=EN>

Honduran sanitary authorities called the government to supply funds to
fight the dengue epidemic. Official reports number the cases at 22 123,
including 1060 with the hemorrhagic strain, and 12 have died. The current
figures surpass the 2006 reports, with 5200 cases of classic dengue, 63
with hemorrhagic and 5 fatalities.
Interim health minister Jenny Meza requested some USD 423 000 to assist the
capital and 3 departments [equivalent to states or provinces. - Mod.TY]
that already issued an alert since the rainy season is not over.
